          "email": "jrh3@att.com",
          "username": "jrh3"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-08-06 13:42:11.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\n> > Patch Set 1:\n > >\n > > (1 comment)\n > \n > Hi Jim, you're right, it has been a decision on last Friday daily\n > to go with the same version for all policy projets.\n > \n > SnakeYAML backward compatibility has been broken in v1.20 and fixed\n > in v1.22.\n > 1.24 is the last released version.\n > \n > The change would be applied to following repos :\n > * apex-pdp\n > * api\n > * common\n > * distribution\n > * docker\n > * drools-applications\n > * drools-pdp\n > * engine\n > * models\n > * pap\n > * xacml-pdp\n > \n > To validate the change, all these repos has been loaded locally to\n > unit tested successfully.\n\nRight.  I wasn't concerned about having a common version, I just wasn't sure it was needed in all of the repos.  However, if it is, then this seems like the right place to do it.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
